description:
&lt;p&gt;Are you ambitious, motivated and passionate about nursing?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Do you want to make a real difference to every one of your patients?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Do you want to work in a clinical area where no two days are the same?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;C5 is a busy acute medical Gastroenterology/Hepatology ward. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The patient group is complex, presenting with conditions including; pre and post transplant liver care; acute/chronic liver disease; oesophageal strictures and cancers; inflammatory bowel disease; eating disorders and patients that require nutritional support. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are dedicated to providing the optimum care for this group of patients and work as an integral part of a multidisciplinary team to enable us to achieve this. The team includes the IBD and stoma nurses; dieticians; nutrition nurses; hepatology nurse specialists and the alcohol specialist nurse service. As a key member of the team you will play a pivotal role in ensuring the delivery of optimal quality care and safety.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We can offer a very supportive team environment and in house courses to develop for personal and professional progression. If you feel you may be the person for this role or ready to take the next step in your career please contact us to discuss.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Informal visits prior to interview are welcome, please contact Davide Sanzullo on 02392 286000 EXT 4664.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing Date 24/11/2020&lt;/p&gt;
